IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: SUPPORT COMMUNITY-BASED ORGANIZATIONS THAT PROVIDE HEALTH CARE TO UNDESERVED COMMUNITIES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: NWRPCA SUPPORTS AND ADVOCATES FOR COMMUNITY-BASED ORGANIZATIONS THAT PROVIDE HIGH-QUALITY, COST EFFECTIVE, COMPREHENSIVE HEALTH CARE SERVICES TO UNDERSERVED COMMUNITES IN THE PACIFIC NORTHWEST, WITHOUT REGARD TO FINANCIAL OR OTHER STATUS.
IRS990.Desc: NWRPCA ORGANIZES AND HOLDS CONFERENCES, WEBINARS, AND OTHER TRAINING PROGRAMS THAT INCLUDE A WIDE VARIETY OF TOPICS RELEVANT TO COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS AND THEIR PARTNERS. NWRPCA PROVIDES TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE AND INFORMATION TO COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS AROUND HUMAN RESOURCES, WORKFORCE RECRUITMENT, RETENTION AND MANAGEMENT, FINANCIAL MANAGEMENT, POLICY ANALYSIS AND ADVOCACY, MIGRANT HEALTH SERVICES, SOCIAL DETERMINANTS OF HEALTH, QUALITY IMPROVEMENT, AND OTHER AREAS OF CONCERN OR INTEREST, USING A VARIETY OF DELIVERY MODALITIES INCLUDING A MONTHLY NEWSLETTER, SITE VISITS, INTRODUCTION TO/FACILITATION OF WORK WITH PARTNERS AND SUBJECT MATTER EXPERTS, DATA ANALYSIS AND DATA PRODUCTS SUCH AS A SALARY SURVEY, AND THE AFORMENTIONED TRAINING AND CONFERENCES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE HAS DETERMINED THAT THE ORGANIZATION IS A TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATION UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA REQUIRE MANAGEMENT TO EVALUATE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN AND RECOGNIZE A TAX LIABILITY IF THE ORGANIZATION HAS TAKEN AN UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY THE U.S. GOVERNMENT. THE ORGANIZATION HAS ANALYZED THE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN AND HAS CONCLUDED THAT AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2022, THERE ARE NO UNCERTAIN POSITIONS TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN THAT WOULD REQUIRE RECOGNITION OF A LIABILITY OR DISCLOSURE IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: SCHOLARSHIPS TO ATTEND ATSU AND GO ON ROTATIONS

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES TRAVEL SCHOLARSHIPS TO INDIVIDUALS AT A FLAT FEE PER PERSON. INDIVIDUALS REGISTER AND APPLY AT THE ANNUAL CONFERENCE. THE ORGANIZATION ALSO PROVIDES STIPENDS TO AT STILL UNIVERSITY STUDENTS FOR TRAVELING AND HOUSING STIPENDS WHEN THEY ARE DOING THEIR TRAINING ROTATIONS AND OCCASIONALLY TO ONE OF OUR LARGER CONFERENCES.
MANAGEMENT AND THE BOARD DETERMINES DISCRETIONARY BONUSES BASED UPON THE ORGANIZATIONS BUDGET, YEARS WORKED AND BIRTHDAY AWARDS.
THE ORGANIZATION WENT BACK TO IN-PERSON CONFERENCES RATHER THAN ENTIRELY VIRTUAL AT WESTERN FORUM IN APRIL 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING BODY DELEGATES BROAD AUTHORITY TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE. THE NWRPCA BOARD HAS FOUR ELECTED OFFICERS: PRESIDENT, PRESIDENT-ELECT, TREASURER AND SECRETARY. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE CONSISTS OF THE FOUR OFFICERS, THE IMMEDIATE PAST PRESIDENT, AND THREE MEMBERS AT LARGE ELECTED BY AND FROM THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. BY CONVENTION, AT LEAST ONE MEMBER OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITEE IS A CLINICIAN. ACCORDING TO THE BYLAWS, THE TERM FOR OFFICERS AND EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE MEMBERS IS ONE YEAR. BY CONVENTION, THE PRESIDENT AND PRESIDENT-ELECT SERVE TWO CONSECUTIVE TEAMS. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE HAS THE AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE BOARD IN ALL BUT A HANDFUL OF MATTERS. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE MEETS MONTHLY BY CONFERENCE CALL. THE QUORUM FOR MEETINGS IS A MAJORITY OF MEMEBERS. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE HAS AND MAY EXERCISE ALL OF THE AUTHORITY OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IN THE MANAGEMENT OF THE ORGANIZATION, EXCEPT FOR THOSE ITEMS LISTED IN THE BYLAWS AS NOT UNDER THE AUTHORITY OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MEMBERSHIP IN NORTHWEST REGIONAL PRIMARY CARE ASSOCIATION IS DIVIDED INTO FOUR CATEGORIES: -CATEGORY A MEMBERS MUST BE A NON-PROFIT CORPORATIONS EXEMPT UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE U.S. INTERNAL REVENUE CODE, OR PUBLIC CORPORATIONS AND MEET THE ORGANIZATIONAL AND OPERATIONAL REQUIREMENTS FOR FUNDING UNDER SECTION 330 OF THE U.S PUBLIC HEALTH SERVICE. -CATEGORY B MEMBERS MUST BE NON-PROFIT CORPORATIONS EXEMPT UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE U.S. INTERNAL REVENUE CODE, OR PUBLIC CORPORATIONS AND AS JUDGED BY PROTOCOL APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, PROVIDE COMPREHENSIVE PRIMARY HEALTH CARE SERVICES WITH A SPECIFIC MISSION TO SERVICE LOW-INCOME PERSONS. -CATEGORY C MEMBERS MUST BE INDIVIDUALS AFFILIATED WITH NWRPCS MEMBER ORGANIZATIONS, OR AFFILIATED WITH ORGANIZATIONS THAT ARE ENGAGED IN COLLABORATION AND PARTNERSHIP WITH NWPCA AND/OR THAT HAVE A SIMILAR MISSION, GOALS OR OBJECTIVES. -CATEGORY D MEMBERS MUST BE ORGANIZATIONS OR INSTITUTIONS THAT ARE ENGAGED IN COLLABORATION AND PARTNERSHIP WITH NWRPCA AND AS JUDGED BY A PROTOCOL APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, HAVE A SIMILAR MISSION, GOALS, AND OBJECTIVES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE DIRECTORS ARE ELECTED BY AND FROM THE ELIGIBLE CATEGORY A MEMBERSHIP OF THAT STATE AND ARE CONFIRMED BY THE GENERAL MEMBERSHIP AT THE ANNUAL MEMBERSHIP MEETING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE AUTHORITY TO AMEND THE ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION OR BYLAWS IS VESTED IN THE CATEGORY A MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE RETURN WILL BE PRESENTED TO THE FULL BOARD FOR APPROVAL AT THE FIRST BOARD MEETING FOLLOWING COMPLETION OF THE DRAFT. THE BOARD PACKET IS GENERALLY SENT OUT SEVERAL DAYS BEFORE THE BOARD MEETING SO THAT THE BOARD HAS TIME TO RETURN AND FORMULATE QUESTIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD MEMBERS REVIEW AND SIGN CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENTS ANNUALLY. THE COMPLIANCE OFFICER REVIEWS THE ENTIRE COMPLIANCE PLAN, INCLUDING THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND ADHERENCE THERETO ANNUALLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990, PART VI, LINE 15A - COMPENSATION PROCESS FOR TOP OFFICIAL THE BOARD REVIEWS THE CEO'S COMPENSATION ANNUALLY, UTILIZING A PCA SALARY SURVEY CONDUCTED BY NACGC/HRSA; A SALARY FROM ARCHBRIGHT OF CEOS IN SEATTLE AREA NON-PROFITS, AND INTERNAL SALARY DATA. FORM 990, PART VI, LINE 15B - COMPENSATION PROCESS FOR OFFICERS NWRPCA COMMISSIONS ARCHBRIGHT TO CONDUCT A BIENNIAL SALARY SURVEY FOR ALL STAFF POSITIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS UPON REQUEST.
